Arthritis Drug To Be Free For Medicare

WASHINGTON (AP) -- A new drug for rheumatoid arthritis is now
available for free to Medicare-enrolled senior citizens who lack
prescription drug coverage.

http://www.intelihealth.com/IH/ihtIH/EMIHC000/333/333/359835.html 
_


White House To Propose Medicare Changes

FORT HOOD, Texas (AP) -- The Bush administration later this month
will propose sweeping changes to Medicare, moving to include a
prescription drug benefit for seniors in the government program,
administration officials said Friday.

http://www.intelihealth.com/IH/ihtIH/EMIHC000/333/333/359756.html 
_


Indian Scientists Discuss Cheaper Treatment For Arthritis

NEW DELHI, India (AP) -- Medical scientists from India and abroad
met Friday to explore making cheaper medicines for treatment of
rheumatoid arthritis -- a disease afflicting more than 50 million
people worldwide.

http://www.intelihealth.com/IH/ihtIH/EMIHC000/333/333/359768.html
_


